  "texts": [
    "115 Lingard [144] 2023 Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to the phenomenon where AI generates content that confidently presents as legitimate-sounding material but is not real.",
    "116 Woodland [145] 2023 Health/ Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to a situation where the generated text is not derived from a factual source but instead arises from statistical predictions of words that are likely to follow the given input.",
    "117 Kashangura [146] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" is the generation or production of a factually invalid statement, characterized by confident output from AI that is not correct or not real. 118 Walker et al.",
    "[147] 2023 Health \"AI hallucinations\" known as wrong or out of context answers generated by ChatGPT AI.",
